        Forschungsumgebung / beta maṣāḥǝft Felber Brill Brill Dār al-ʻilm lil-malāyīn,  IslHornAfr: Islam in the Horn of Africa, A Comparative Literary Approach. European Research Council (Advanced Grant no. 322849)</dc:publisher><dcterms:isPartOf rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu"/><dcterms:bibliographicCitation>PRS0115IHA</dcterms:bibliographicCitation><dc:format>xml</dc:format><dc:language rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#language">en</dc:language><dc:language rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#language">ar</dc:language><dc:contributor>Alessandro Gori</dc:contributor><dc:contributor>P. Bearman, Th. Bianquis, C.E. Bosworth, E. van Donzel, W.P. Heinrichs</dc:contributor><foaf:gender>male</foaf:gender><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://betamasaheft.eu/ontology/pers"/><foaf:name xml:lang="ar">البكري, محمد بن محمد ابو الحسن بن محمد بن عبد الرحمان الصديقي </foaf:name><foaf:name>al-Bakrī, Muḥammad b. Muḥammad Abū al-Ḥasan b. Muḥammad b. ʻAbd al-Raḥmān al-Ṣiddīqī </foaf:name><foaf:name xml:lang="ar">ابو المكارم شمس الدين</foaf:name><foaf:name>Abū al-Makārim Šams al-Dīn</foaf:name><foaf:name xml:lang="ar">القطب البكري</foaf:name><foaf:name>al-Quṭb al-Bakrī</foaf:name><foaf:name xml:lang="ar">البكري الكبير</foaf:name><foaf:name>al-Bakrī al-Kabīr</foaf:name><foaf:name xml:lang="ar">سيدي محمد البكري</foaf:name><foaf:name>Sayyidī Muḥammad al-Bakrī</foaf:name><crm:P4_has_time_span><crm:E52_Time-span><rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/E67_Birth"/><crm:P78_is_identified_by>0930 </crm:P78_is_identified_by></crm:E52_Time-span></crm:P4_has_time_span><crm:P4_has_time_span><crm:E52_Time-span><rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/E69_Death"/><crm:P78_is_identified_by>0994 </crm:P78_is_identified_by></crm:E52_Time-span></crm:P4_has_time_span><crm:P4_has_time_span><crm:E52_Time-span><crm:P78_is_identified_by>10th / 16th century (d. 952 / 1545)Egyptian poet, mystic and Šāfiʻī scholar. Author of al-Ḥizb.

The additional names given above are based on al-Ziriklī.

al-Ziriklī notes that Brockelmann mixes his biography with that of his father Abū al-Ḥasan al-Bakrī. The mix-up is repeated in Encyclopaedia of Islam, where the entry on al-Bakrī is written by Brockelmann.
               </crm:P78_is_identified_by></crm:E52_Time-span></crm:P4_has_time_span></rdf:Description></rdf:RDF>